tical purges, asphyxiating modernity, violence, and indoctrination in the name of progress. Nguyen Thanh Hien’s Chronicles of a Village, the writer’s first work to be translated into English, is an elegy for a place and a people; a profound meditation on how history is created, destroyed, manipulated, and rewritten; and a tribute to the beauty and ";fatal historical disabilities of a land."  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 02. Jun 2024) 7aLITERARY CRITICISM / General.2bisacsh1 aNguyen-Hoang, Quyen, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb40uhttps://doi.org/10.12987/9780300278392?locatt=mode:legacy40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780300278392423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780300278392/original  aEBA_EMB  aGBV-deGruyter-alles